Now you need to add your hello program into the QNX boot image.

"cd ~/qnx-from-board-up/blog3"
"nano image.build"

Paste this content (based on the blog):

[virtual=x86_64,multiboot] boot = {
    startup-x86 -D 8250
    procnto-smp-instr
}

[+fsys] root = {
    /hello
}

[+script] init = {
    display_msg "Hello World from QNX"
    exec /hello
}


What changed we did?

Added a filesystem section [+fsys] root = {...} to include /hello in the image.
In the init script:
                  Show a message via display_msg
                  Run your user-space program with exec /hello

 Save and exit.
